					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes; I could also use MMC5 if it needs 8x8 attributes and extra audio. (If using any complicated mapper and not all features are used, the features used could be specified in a README file, so that a less complicated cartridge can be used.) If it is not needed, other mappers can be used; in many cases, NROM is good enough. (In a project I am working on at this time, NROM is more than sufficient. In another idea, I planned it on paper it seem this my idea of mapper would help.)<br /><br />For implementing the mapper, I had no intention that <em>any</em> emulator authors would implement this mapper; instead, they should be a DotFami mapper code, and have the emulator include a compiler from DotFami mapper codes into native code, and emulate the mapper that way instead.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="gopher://zzo38computer.org/" class="postlink">.</a></div>
